                " and width 0.57 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The primary gamma ray data following resonance-",
                " averaged neutron capture (arc), although appearing in",
                " the main reference, have not been included in this",
                " EXFOR work."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Measurement of gammas from thermal capture."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".GAMS1,2,3 bent crystal spectrometers:",
                "   gams1, range 35-500 keV, energy resolution (FWHM",
                "   in eV) was 5.5e-06*e(g)squ(keV)/N, where N is the",
                "   order of diffraction.",
                "   GAMS2/3, range 150-1500 keV, the energy resolution",
                "   (fwhm in eV) was 2.E-6*e(g)squ(keV)/N.",
                "   Energy calibration of the measured gamma-rays was",
                "   performed by making a best fit to the reported",
                "   values of the plutonium K-alpha1 and K-alpha2",
                "   energies 103.741+-0.002 and 99.521+-0.002-keV,",
                "   respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
